  "prompt": "What did George Lucas think of the Force Awakens?",
  "response": "George Lucas had mixed feelings about \"Star Wars: The Force Awakens.\" He was consulted during the film's development, but he did not have any creative control over the project. In interviews, Lucas expressed that he enjoyed the movie and thought it was well-made. However, he also mentioned that he felt the film was too nostalgic and relied too heavily on elements from the original trilogy, rather than introducing more new and original content. Despite these criticisms, Lucas seemed generally supportive of the new direction the franchise was taking under Disney's leadership.",
